25/06/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- War crimes prosecutors pressed charges Thursday (June 24th) against four former members of a paramilitary group for war crimes against civilians committed in Croatia. The four allegedly took part in the 1991 killings of six non-Serbs in the Beli Manastir municipality. Zoran Vuksic, Slobodan Strigic, Branko Hrnjak and Velimir Bertic are also charged with inhumane treatment of civilians. They are all citizens of Serbia. (B92, Beta, HRT - 24/06/10)
